title: Youth football: McCann, Tilley star for Little Warriors
text: Posted Oct. 1, 2015 at 1:06 PM By Staff Reports Posted Oct. 1, 2015 at 1:06 PM Â» Social News The following are game summaries from last week's play for the Little Warriors youth football team. Information is provided by the coaches. The Little Warriors Pee Wee A team beat Timberlane, 40-6 last Saturday and improved to 3-0 on the season. The Little Warriors rushed for more than 300 yards led by Tucker McCann who ran for 100 yards and scored a touchdown and ran in a 2-point conversion. Chris Capezzuto and Owen Bateman each had two touchdowns, while Kyle Tilley had one. Ben McClelland, Thomas MacDougall, Bodey Reed, Jack McCann, Cam MacHardy and Zach Fredericks starred on the offensive line. Defensively, Colin Harrington led the team with eight tackles, while Nico Zaino had six and Joe Larrabee had four. MacDougall had an interception, while Liam Considine, Jack McCann and Jason Pinsonnault all had a quarterback sack. Pee Wee B The Little Warriors improved to 3-0 with a 14-6 at Timberlane last Saturday. Kevin Tilley had both touchdowns, while Frank Brown ran in a conversion. Benjamin Goodwin, Quinn MacNeil, Brandon Matheson, Jason Pinsonnault, Tony Johnson, LeBron Miller, Jake Fredericks and Nolan Perkins led the offensive line. Defensively, Tilley, Fredericks, Brown, Pinsonnault, Miller, MacNeil, Matthew Mattimore, David Bagley, and Nolan Perkins all starred. By Staff Reports
